  Philosophic Mercury — the purified and potentized water that serves as the
  bridge between kingdoms. The student must learn to distinguish between "dead"
  distilled water and "living" alchemical mercury. The pedagogical peak is the
  Quarter I Gathering, where students share their experiences with the long
  putrefaction and the Gur. Monitor students for their understanding of
  receptivity; without a receptive mind, the water work remains opaque.
]

