= ⬡ QUARTER I GATHERING — Descent into Water

*Theme:* Sharing first water work experiences; philosophical discussion of putrefaction.

#hm-note[
  Use this gathering to check for "Raven's Head" fatigue. The long wait for the
  Gur can be demoralizing for students used to the faster pace of plant work.
  Reiterate the alchemist's primary virtue: Patience.
]

*Students bring:*
- Their dew collection journals.
- Their fermented and/or distilled water preparations in whatever stage.
- A reflection on what the study of putrefaction has revealed about their understanding of death and renewal.
- Questions that have arisen about the relationship between plant work (Year One) and water work.

